result.execSummary:
The defendant Dane A Dzubinski was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possession of Narcotic Drugs, a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(am).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Maintain absolute sobriety. No use or possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription. -Operate a motor vehicle with a valid driver's license.

-If Probation/Extended Supervision is revoked and/or a prison term ordered, outstanding financial obligations shall be collected pursuant to statutory provisions, including deductions from inmate prison monies.  If discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered against the defendant and in favor of restitution victims and government entities for outstanding financial obligations.  Collections may include income assignment.

2:04 PM Defendant Dane A Dzubinski in court.  Attorney Steven Hughes in court for Dane A Dzubinski.  Prosecuting attorney Christian Farina in court for the State of Wisconsin. 
Case called for plea and sentencing.
Court conducts plea colloquy.  Defendant enters a guilty plea to Counts 3 and 5.  Court finds defendant guilty.   Counts 1, 2, 4 and 5 are dismissed and read in.
Recommendations by the State.  Recommendations by the Defense. Statement by defendant. 

The Court Orders the Following:

Count 1:
3 Years Imprisonment (Credit - 61 Days) CONCURRENT with 21CF1692
-	1 Years of Initial Confinement
-	2 Years of Extended Supervision

Defendant is eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program
Defendant is eligible for the Substance Abuse Program

Conditions of Extended Supervision:
-	AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
-	Absolute Sobriety; 
-	Random U.A.'s;
-	No Use or Possession of alcohol or illegal drugs or drug paraphernalia;
-	No use or possession of any controlled substances without a valid doctor's prescription
-	All prescriptions to be filled at the same pharmacy
-	Inform agent of all prescriptions;
-	Complete a minimum of 20 hours community service during each year of extended supervision;
-	Operate a Motor Vehicle only with a Valid Driver's License;
-	No new law violations;

COSTS:  $ 268.00

DNA Surcharge: $ 250.00

DNA Sample ordered and to be provided immediately if in custody or within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department. 

Total costs/fine/forfeiture:  Cash bail from 22CF950 to be applied costs and surcharges in 22CF950 and 21CF1692.  Any remaining financial obligations to be paid as a condition of extended supervision within the first 12 months of extended supervision. Failure to pay;  will result in a civil judgment.

Felony warnings, immigration warnings, voting rights and firearms warnings given.

10:29 AM; Case called for Bail/bond hearing.  Defendant Dane A Dzubinski in court, in custody at WCJ, with attorney Steven Hughes.   Abbey Nickolie appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Atty. Hughes is asking the court to address his motion to modify bail filed on 7/13/22.  Court takes a moment to review the motion.  Atty. Hughes presents arguments; he is requesting the cash bail be lowered or defendant be granted Huber bailee status.  Atty. Nickolie objects and presents arguments.  For reasons placed on the record the Court grants Defendant's Motion to Modify Bail; Court will modify cash bond to $1000.00 with the same conditions, but to include that the defendant must maintain full time employment.  Court inquires how the matter will be proceeding.  Atty. Hughes provides an upate; he is asking the matter just remain on the calendar as previously scheduled for August 8th.  Court will maintain the 08/08/2022 hearing at 9:00 a.m.

08:35 AM Defendant Dane A Dzubinski in court, in custody, with attorney Steven Hughes.   Kevin Michael Osborne appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Attorney Osborne notes the Officer in this matter has not appeared this morning and would be asking for the preliminary hearing to be held later this morning in attempt to get a witness here or adjourn to Wednesday with the understanding that it would be outside of the 10 days.  Attorney Hughes states he is unavailable this morning or Wednesday and would request for the defendant to be released from custody and this matter be dismissed.  The Court will hold the preliminary hearing morning so Attorney Hughes is to come back when he is available.  Court takes a recess at 8:37 AM.  Matter recalled at 10:52 AM with the same appearances.  Assistant District Attorney Randy Sitzberger sworn in and testifies on direct by Attorney Osborne.  Cross examination by Attorney Hughes.  State rests.  State moves for bind over without argument.  Attorney Hughes objects to bind over with argument.  Court finds probable cause to believe that a felony was committed and binds the defendant over for trial.  Waive reading of Information.  NOT GUILTY PLEA ENTERED.  Bail remains as fixed.  Hearing scheduled for August 8, 2022 at 10:00 am.
